main event: A witness observed 10 to 20 unidentified flying objects descending near Sweet Springs, Missouri on February 19, 1958, which appeared to crash without visible results.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be dark colored and had red and white features., The duration of the observation lasted between 10 to 15 seconds., Witnesses reported seeing a hole in the ice of a small pond where the object was believed to have fallen., A ground search and aerial surveillance conducted by the Air Force returned negative results., Witnesses described the object as being metallic and elongated in shape.
witness description: Mr. ***** and Trooper Roberts; witnesses described Mr. ***** as reliable and of good character.
